                <mxCell id="TOOL_IO" value="&lt;b&gt;Import / export tools&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;Moves data between LEAP + Python&lt;br&gt;Move models between LEAP areas&lt;div&gt;Intended to be as simple as possible but because of the way LEAP API is designed, it is currently very finnicky.&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;fillColor=#E6FAF8;strokeColor=#3BA7A2;fontColor=#000000;fontSize=14;" parent="L_TOOL" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1240" y="340" width="320" height="118" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="L_INTEG" value="Integration" style="layer;fontSize=14;" parent="1"/>
                <mxCell id="LEAP_AREA" value="Single integrated LEAP Area" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontStyle=1;spacing=10;fillColor=#F3F1EC;strokeColor=#8C7B6D;fontColor=#000000;fontSize=16;" parent="L_INTEG" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1300" y="620" width="120" height="156" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="L_NOTES" value="Notes" style="layer;fontSize=14;" parent="1"/>
                <mxCell id="N_DEMAND" value="Demand notes&lt;br&gt;-Has the most potential for change in method.&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;-Input data is integral to method. e.g. without stocks, transport stock flow model cannot be used.&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;-Input data needs to be maintained. For transport this doesnt have a structured process but it may need one.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-pipelines activity link from gas and oil supply helps to align pipeline energy use with supply assumptions.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;fillColor=#F7F7F7;strokeColor=#BDBDBD;fontSize=14;" parent="L_NOTES" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="30" y="1730" width="370" height="280" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="N_TRANS" value="Transformation notes&lt;br&gt;-Power model is designed so it can use the more simple LEAP process or the NEMO process which provides more flexibility.&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;-Many processes can be designed with a lot of complexity (e.g. hydrogen, refining, gas). How to manage this so we don&#39;t overreach?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-All fuels have supply links because they may be traded. this interaction with &#39;supply&#39; isnt very clear.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;fillColor=#F7F7F7;strokeColor=#BDBDBD;fontSize=14;" parent="L_NOTES" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="430" y="1740" width="370" height="280" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="N_SUP" value="Supply notes&lt;br&gt;-most modelling work is in assumptions development, such as capacity and trade assesment. For this reason the real supply modellers are not likely to be invovled in using LEAP, instead focused on qualitative aspects and simple spreadsheet analysis mainly." style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;fillColor=#F7F7F7;strokeColor=#BDBDBD;fontSize=14;" parent="L_NOTES" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="830" y="1740" width="420" height="280" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="N_INT" value="Integration &amp;amp; open questions&lt;br&gt;- major concern about LEAP performance when multiple models for many economies are merged. Should test this early.&lt;div&gt;- How should assumption development be done? How long should it take? Should it consider all elements of the model... but that is quite complex? Many economies will change their trajectories during the modelling process, how do we handle that?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- when a new fuel becomes important or is realised to be missing, how do we incorporate it into the modelling?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;fillColor=#F7F7F7;strokeColor=#BDBDBD;fontSize=14;" parent="L_NOTES" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="1300" y="1730" width="320" height="280" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="3Vn5BuMNg00IzMXtSu-n-98" value="To do list&lt;div&gt;- Develop 9th replica for all models (where useful they can be designed differently)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Macro modelling&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Leap export to energy balances formatting (using same format as esto energy balances)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- ESTO energy balances format&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;- Visualisation (we will use 9th edition system and balances format until this is ready)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt;-Costs&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacing=8;fillColor=#F7F7F7;strokeColor=#BDBDBD;fontSize=14;" parent="L_NOTES" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="-320" y="1730" width="320" height="280" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="E_X_COAL_TO_LOSS" value="" style="endArrow=block;html=1;rounded=0;exitX=0;exitY=0.5;exitPerimeter=1;entryX=1;entryY=0.5;entryPerimeter=1;fontSize=14;" parent="1" source="G_X_COAL" target="L_LOSS_COAL" edge="1">
                    <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="3" value="Other models and projects" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=center;verticalAlign=middle;fontStyle=1;spacing=6;fillColor=#f8cecc;strokeColor=#b85450;fontSize=16;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="-340" y="40" width="280" height="40" as="geometry"/>
